Rating: 4
I have made this recipe many times. I've used it with the Dark Chocolate Souffles and I've used it to make ice cream. I also use the ice cream with a base of chocolate brownie, scoop of ice cream and a drizzle of ganache. Amazing! This recipe never disappoints.

Rating: 4
The cardamom creme anglaise was fantastic, absolutely top-notch. Would be a great accompaniment to many desserts. I wasn't particularly pleased with the individual soufflés paired with this recipe. I used 1 1/2 tablespoons powdered cardamom instead of 2 tablespoons of crushed pods.

Rating: 4
This is absolutely delicious. I made one mistake by purchasing crushed cardamom and still using 2 tbsp. So there was a lot in it but still tasty.

